description.plain:
HAIM (pronounced high-em, from the Hebrew word for life,  חַיִּים) is a rock band from Los Angeles, California. The band comprises sisters Este (b. March 14th, 1986), Danielle (b. February 16th, 1989) and Alana Haim (b. December 15th, 1991) as well as keyboardist Tommy King, and drummer Jody Giachello [citation needed].

Haim’s sound has been described as “nu-folk-meets-nineties-R&B” and “music that sounds like it was written on a lakeside retreat attended by Stevie Nicks, John Waite and En Vogue.” Their first full length album, Days Are Gone, was released in 2013. They played at the 2013 Glastonbury festival, earned a top ranking in BBC’s Sound of 2013 poll, and signed with Jay-Z’s Roc Nation management group.

Their second full-length album Something To Tell You was released on July 7, 2017.

songs.title: Gasoline

description.plain:
Off of HAIM’s 2020 album Women In Music Pt. III, “Gasoline” is a sexy track about a possibly-dysfunctional relationship.

Said Danielle Haim:

“That slowed-down ending is due to Ariel. He had this crazy EDM filter he stuck on the guitar, and I was like, ‘Yes, that’s fucking perfect.’”

The band recorded a live performance of the track for Jimmy Kimmel Live. The video was shot during the summer of the 2020 COVID-19 pandemic in the empty parking lot of the “The Forum”, a music venue in Inglewood, California:
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=NCWSSTQb3qw

A remix featuring Taylor Swift was released on February 18th, 2021, and featured on the extended edition of Women In Music Pt III.

songs.title: Now I’m In It

description.plain:
“Now I’m In It” is the second single from HAIM’s upcoming third album. It was released, alongside its video, on October 30th, 2019. https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=G-UnzRM24IM

Despite its lyrics, Danielle Haim has clarified that the song is not about a break up, but about mental health – struggling between yourself and your mind.
